seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Account Balance: Active Accounts Only: 50th Percentile
seriess.notes: The 50th percentile account balance among active credit card accounts. The total outstanding balance for the account at the end of the current month's cycle. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. Therefore, some credit card accounts that are defined as active will have a zero balance. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Account Balance: Active Accounts Only: 75th Percentile
seriess.notes: The 75th percentile account balance among active credit card accounts. The total outstanding balance for the account at the end of the current month's cycle. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. Therefore, some credit card accounts that are defined as active will have a zero balance. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Account Balance: Active Accounts Only: 90th Percentile

Therefore, some credit card accounts that are defined as active will have a zero balance. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Utilization: Active Accounts Only: 50th Percentile
seriess.notes: The 50th percentile credit utilization rate among credit card accounts. The utilization rate represents the share of the available credit line that the borrower is utilizing. It is defined as the cycle ending balance divided by the current credit limit. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. Therefore, some credit card accounts that are defined as active will still have zero utilization of the available credit line. Available credit lines of inactive accounts are not included. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Utilization: Active Accounts Only: 75th Percentile
seriess.notes: The 75th percentile credit utilization rate among credit card accounts. The utilization rate represents the share of the available credit line that the borrower is utilizing. It is defined as the cycle ending balance divided by the current credit limit. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. Therefore, some credit card accounts that are defined as active will still have zero utilization of the available credit line. Available credit lines of inactive accounts are not included. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Utilization: Active Accounts Only: 90th Percentile
seriess.notes: The 90th percentile credit utilization rate among credit card accounts. The utilization rate represents the share of the available credit line that the borrower is utilizing. It is defined as the cycle ending balance divided by the current credit limit. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. Therefore, some credit card accounts that are defined as active will still have zero utilization of the available credit line. Available credit lines of inactive accounts are not included. seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Percentage of Accounts Subject to Promotional APR: Percentage APR Accounts
seriess.notes:
The share of active credit card accounts that have a positive balance subject to a promotional APR. Promotional APRs are defined as APRs priced at a rate below the account holder's normal purchase APR at the end of the most recent cycle. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months.

For more detail see the methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Average Purchase APR: General Purpose
seriess.notes:
The average purchase (nonpromotional) APR for active general purpose credit card accounts using the APR reported at quarter end. Any reported values below 5 percent are assumed to be promotional APRs and are therefore excluded. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months.

For more detail see the methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Average Purchase APR: Private Label
seriess.notes:
The average purchase (nonpromotional) APR for active private label credit card accounts, using the APR reported at quarter end. Any reported values below 5 percent are assumed to be promotional APRs and are therefore excluded. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months.

For more detail see the methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: 30 or More Days Past Due Rates: Balances Based
seriess.notes: The share of total credit card balances that are 30 or more days past due. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: 60 or More Days Past Due Rates: Balances Based
seriess.notes: The share of total credit card balances that are 60 or more days past due. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: 90 or More Days Past Due Rates: Balances Based
seriess.notes: The share of total credit card balances that are 90 or more days past due. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Revolving Balances Only
seriess.notes: The total revolved dollar balances as of quarter end for accounts that revolved all or some portion of their cycle ending balance. Revolving balances are calculated for these revolving accounts as the sum total of the prior cycle ending balances less actual payments made on the prior cycle ending balances. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Total Balances
seriess.notes: The total outstanding balance for all consumer credit card accounts among firms included in the reporting panel. Reported balances are as of the end of the current month's cycle. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Total Commitments
seriess.notes: The total dollar amount of all consumer credit card commitments among firms included in the reporting panel. Reported commitments are as of the current month's cycle. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Current Credit Limit: 50th Percentile
seriess.notes: The 50th percentile credit limit among credit card accounts. The current credit limit is the maximum available credit on the account. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Current Credit Limit: 75th Percentile
seriess.notes: The 75th percentile credit limit among credit card accounts. The current credit limit is the maximum available credit on the account. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Current Credit Limit: 90th Percentile
seriess.notes: The 90th percentile credit limit among credit card accounts. The current credit limit is the maximum available credit on the account. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Net Charge-Off Rate
seriess.notes:
The annualized net charge-off rate for all credit card accounts. Net charge-offs refer to the three-month sum of gross charge-offs less recoveries. The annualized net charge-off rate is calculated as four times the total quarterly net charge-offs divided by the three-month average for total outstanding credit card balances. 

For more detail see the methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Number of Accounts
seriess.notes: The total count of all consumer credit card accounts among firms included in the reporting panel. Reported accounts are as of the end of the current month's cycle. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Percentage of Accounts with Credit Line Decrease
seriess.notes: The share of total credit card accounts in the quarter that experienced a bank-initiated or borrower-requested credit line decrease. Note that the time series data for Credit Line Decrease begins in 2012Q4 because this was the first quarter when the data were of sufficient quality to begin reporting. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Percentage of Accounts with Credit Line Increase
seriess.notes: The share of total credit card accounts in the quarter that experienced a bank-initiated or borrower-requested credit line increase. Note that the time series data for Credit Line Decrease begins in 2012Q4 because this was the first quarter when the data were of sufficient quality to begin reporting. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Average Purchase Volume by Credit Score Group: 660-719 Credit Score
seriess.notes:
The average quarterly total purchase volume per active credit card account with a current credit score from 660 to 719. An account's purchase volume is the net sum for the three months within the quarter. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. 

For more detail see the methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Average Purchase Volume by Credit Score Group: >=720 Credit Score
seriess.notes:

An account's purchase volume is the net sum for the three months within the quarter. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. 

For more detail see the methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Average Purchase Volume by Credit Score Group: <660 Credit Score
seriess.notes:

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Total Purchase Volume
seriess.notes:
The cumulative net purchase volume for credit card accounts during the quarter. Net purchase volume measures the aggregate dollar amount of purchases made during the current month's cycle, less any returns. Cash advance and balance transfer volumes are excluded.

For more detail see the methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.notes: The 50th percentile credit score among credit card accounts. The current credit score is the most recently determined commercially available credit score of the primary account holder. seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Share of Accounts Making the Full Balance Payment
seriess.notes: The share of credit card accounts paying the full account balance. Payment behavior (Active Accounts Only) variables indicate the payment behavior of active credit card accounts in the final month of the quarter. When an account has a zero-cycle ending balance, the prior month's payment behavior is used to properly classify the account. Payment behavior shares do not sum to 100 percent because active accounts with a zero or negative cycle ending balance or missing payment information are not shown nor are active accounts that made no payment or a payment that was less than the minimum. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Share of Accounts Making Greater Than the Minimum Payment but Less Than the Full Balance
seriess.notes: The share of credit card accounts making payment above the minimum payment and below the full balance. Payment behavior (Active Accounts Only) variables indicate the payment behavior of active credit card accounts in the final month of the quarter. When an account has a zero-cycle ending balance, the prior month's payment behavior is used to properly classify the account. Payment behavior shares do not sum to 100 percent because active accounts with a zero or negative cycle ending balance or missing payment information are not shown nor are active accounts that made no payment or a payment that was less than the minimum. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Credit Card Balances: Share of Accounts Making the Minimum Payment

Payment behavior shares do not sum to 100 percent because active accounts with a zero or negative cycle ending balance or missing payment information are not shown nor are active accounts that made no payment or a payment that was less than the minimum. Active credit card accounts are defined as credit card accounts that are open and have had debit, credit, or balance activity in the last 12 months. seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Mortgage Balances: 30 or More Days Past Due: Including Foreclosures Rates: Accounts Based
seriess.notes: Share of first-lien accounts 30 or more days past due. All past due active mortgages are included in the days past due calculations, including foreclosures. Borrowers who qualify for forbearance and stop making payments are also recorded as past due for all past due rate calculations. Days past due rates are presented using the number of accounts (accounts based). For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

seriess.title: Large Bank Consumer Mortgage Balances: 60 or More Days Past Due: Including Foreclosures Rates: Accounts Based

Borrowers who qualify for forbearance and stop making payments are also recorded as past due for all past due rate calculations. Days past due rates are presented using the number of accounts (accounts based). For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).

Front-end DTI is reported at origination. For more detail see: methodology (https://sc103-philfed-prod-cm.sitecore-prod-ase4.appserviceenvironment.net/surveys-and-data/y14-methodology).
